should be made for five years in advance, as had been done under Caesar3 the intention probably was to establish the custom of each year designating those who should hold office five years later. Those who at present were in command of legions-legati pro praetore, many of whom were not yet of praetorian rank—were to be appointed at once to the praetorship, while the rest of the appointments for the five years were to be made by the em- eror.
